    "media:imagetext": "K5054\nThe Civic Centre, Southampton\nOPENING OF THE R.JMA CHELL\n40th ANNIVERSARY\nOF 1st FLIGHT OF\nTHE SPITFIRE\nSOUTHAMPTON 5th MARCH 1976\nFLOWN IN SPITFIRE IA P7350\nPilot - Sqn. Ldr. R. M. Raw, A.F.C.\nTime - 1500 5 March 1976\nOverflown Southampton in salute\nto R. J. Mitchell's prototype Spitfire\n40th ANNIVERSARY\nK. J. Mitchell Committee\nThe R. J. Mitchell Hall\nKingsonuge Lane\nSouthampton, SO1 OGB\nTo commemorate the first flight of the 'SPITFIRE' from\nSouthampton (Eastleigh) Airport on the 5th March 1936.\nThe 'SPITFIRE' was designed by R. J. Mitchell and built\nSupermarine Works, Woolston, Southampton",
